---
By: Ralph W. Trine
Locus:
  Page: 471
  Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Thoughts
---
Of all the known forms of energy, thought is the most subtle, the
irresistible force. It has always been operating; but, as far as the great
masses of the people are concerned, it has been operating blindly, or,
rather, they have been blind to its mighty power, except in the cases of a
few here and there.
